sec.p:
Inclusion criteria include:
(1) The research topic is the application of artificial intelligence in the design of knee joint prostheses, size prediction, model identification or surgical planning;
(2) The research type is clinical study, retrospective study, prospective study or technical validation study;
(3) Provide clear performance evaluation indicators (such as accuracy rate, F1 score, AUC, MAE, etc.);
(4) The publication language is English.

Exclusion criteria include:
(1) Studies not related to knee joint prostheses (such as hip joints, dental implants);
(2) Studies without reported quantitative results or only descriptive studies;
(3) Conference abstracts, reviews, and other types of literature;
(4) Studies for which full texts cannot be obtained or whose data are incomplete.

Given the high heterogeneity in methodology, evaluation indicators, and clinical scenarios across the included studies, a meta-analysis was not feasible. Instead, we adopted a descriptive synthesis approach to summarize and categorize the research characteristics, technical paths, performance, and clinical significance. The focus was on the following dimensions:
(1) Basic research characteristics (time distribution, geographical origin, sample size);
(2) Classification of artificial intelligence application directions (prosthetic size prediction, model identification, surgical planning and design);
(3) Technical method characteristics (model architecture, input data type, evaluation system);
(4) Performance and clinical relevance.
